<1ST_LINE>r w BC-HousePlantClosingRollCall 3Takes   07-14 0480</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-House Plant Closing Roll Call, 3 Takes,</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 286-136 roll call Wednesday by
which the House approved legislation to require companies to give
60 days notice to employees of upcoming plant closings and major
layoffs.
   A ``yes'' vote is for the bill.
   Voting yes were 232 Democrats and 54 Republicans.
   Voting no were 16 Democrats and 120 Republicans.
   X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
