<HEAD>Poll Shows Bentsen Helps Democrats</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Dukakis' choice of Sen. Lloyd
Bentsen of Texas as his running mate helps Democratic ticket in
Louisiana, according to a poll by Mason-Dixon Opinion Research.
   The poll was taken Thursday through Sunday, before Dukakis named
Bentsen as his choice for the vice presidential nomination.
   It showed Dukakis with a slim 45-42 percent margin over
Republican nominee-to-be George Bush, a lead within the poll's
margin of error of plus or minus 3.5 percentage points.
   Asked who they would vote for if Bentsen were added to the
Democratic ticket, the 825 voters who responded to the poll went
for Dukakis by 46 percent to 39 percent for Bush.
   Bentsen, chairman of the Senate Finance Committee, has been a
strong supporter of the oil industry, a key business in Louisiana.
