<HEAD>Baby Trapped In Car Safety Seat Burns to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CASTRO VALLEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A baby trapped in a car safety seat
burned to death when her parents' car burst into flames in the
parking lot of a doctor's office, officials said.
   Najia Nawabi, 16 months, was pronounced dead at the scene of
Wednesday's blaze.
   Two other Nawabi children, 4 and 2{, escaped injury. They
watched in horror as their younger sister perished while two
bystanders tried to rescue her.
   ``I pulled and jerked on that baby seat but it wouldn't budge,''
said Gary Smith of San Leandro. ``The flames completely engulfed
the car. All I wanted was to get the baby out of there.''
   Smith and another bystander, Dr. Mosa Mardanzai, attempted to
unfasten the baby seat, but had to give up when smoke and flames
encircled the screaming infant.
   ``I couldn't see her anymore,'' said a shaken Mardanzai, 47.
   Sheriff's officials said Noorn and Noor Nawabi of Hayward parked
their car in front of the medical center where Noor Nawabi, who is
six months pregnant, had an appointment with her physician.
   Noorn Nawabi stayed in the car with the toddler and the couple's
two sons. At one point, he told authorities, he left the children
alone to check on his wife and the fire broke out while he was gone.
   The cause of the fire was under investigation, said Castro
Valley Fire Marshal Robert Bohman.
