<HEAD>Quotes From the Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, on Jesse Jackson: ``We want him to play an
important role in the campaign. We want his support. We hope and
expect he will be very much involved with us in the campaign and
afterwards.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, hinting at a possible floor fight over the vice
presidential nomination at the Democratic National Convention:
``I'm not suggesting that I will compete for a place on the ticket
but the floor is wide open on Thursday night when the
recommendation is made.''
   
   SEN. LLOYD BENTSEN, on how he would serve as vice president to
Dukakis: ``As vice president of the United States, I would give him
the very best counsel I could when I agreed or disagreed on the
issues. But there's only one president of the United States and
he's the man that bears the ultimate responsibility and pays the
ultimate price.''
