<1ST_LINE>r a PM-FighterCrash     07-14 0194</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Fighter Crash,0198</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>$30 Million Fighter Jet Crashes, Killing Marine Pilot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAVELOCK, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Harrier fighter jet crashed soon after
takeoff on a training mission, killing the Marine pilot, officials
said.
   It was the second fatal crash involving a Harrier based at
Cherry Point Marine Air Station this year.
   The $30 million AV8-B Harrier II went down near Havelock just
after 8 a.m. Wednesday, about a mile south of the air station
runway into the backyard of a mobile home, said Master Sgt. Sandra
Riley, a Marine spokeswoman.
   The jet clipped a stand of trees before it hit the ground and
burned in a rural area off Highway 101, Ms. Riley said.
   The pilot was 1st Lt. Kerry D. Dale, 26, of Havelock, a member
of the Marine Attack Training Squadron 203 and part of the Second
Marine Aircraft Wing. Ms. Riley said Dale had been on a routine
training mission.
   The Harrier is capable of vertical takeoffs and landings but was
not attempting a vertical takeoff when it crashed, Ms. Riley said.
Riley said.
   A team from the air station is investigating the cause of the
crash, Ms. Riley said.
</TEXT>
