<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0432</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sultry Summer Heat Lingers Throughout Much Of The Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A high-pressure system spread a steamy blanket over much of the
nation today, boosting temperatures in the southern and central
Plains and the middle Mississippi Valley.
   Temperatures were already in the 80s this morning, and highs
from the upper 90s to over 100 degrees were forecast for much of
America west of the Mississippi.
   The hot, humid weather was expected to linger through Friday
because of the high-pressure system extending across most of the
western and central sections of the nation.
   Cooler weather in the 50s and 60s prevailed only across the
northern tier. Showers and thunderstorms were scattered along a
cold front curving from upper Michigan into southern Nebraska.
   Strong thunderstorms swept through southern Wisconsin, extreme
northern Illinois and northwestern Missouri. A few showers and
thunderstorms also lingered in eastern Colorado and southwest
Kansas.
   Fair skies prevailed across the rest of the nation.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from Pennsylvania to New York and New England, from southeast
Virginia to North Carolina, northern South Carolina, the southern
Appalachian mountains and Florida.
   Temperatures were predicted in the 60s and 70s in the Pacific
Northwest and along the California coast; the 70s to near 80
degrees in Maine; the 80s from northern New England to the upper
Great Lakes and in northern Montana; from 100 to 105 degrees in
western Kansas, western Oklahoma and parts of the Texas Panhandle;
from 100 to 110 in the desert Southwest, Nevada and Utah; and in
the 90s in the rest of the country.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 49
degrees at Sexton Summit, Ore., to 93 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 75 fair; Boston 70 fair; Buffalo 79 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 78 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 72 foggy; Cleveland
74 fair; Detroit 76 fair; Miami 79 fair; New York 68 foggy;
Philadelphia 73 foggy; Pittsburgh 73 fair; Portland, Maine 66 fair;
Washington 75 hazy.
   _Central: Bismarck 60 fair; Chicago 80 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
82 fair; Denver 72 cloudy; Des Moines 83 fair; Indianapolis 72
foggy; Kansas City 84 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 74 fair; Nashville
76 fair; New Orleans 81 fair; St. Louis 82 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 78 fair; Anchorage 58 cloudy; Las Vegas 82
fair; Los Angeles 64 cloudy; Phoenix 93 fair; Salt Lake City 76
fair; San Diego 64 cloudy; San Francisco 58 fair; Seattle 55 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 70 partly cloudy; Toronto 73 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
