<DOCNO> AP880714-0066 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-07-14-88 0854EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--RaisinRaids     07-14 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Raisin Raids,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Raisin Figurines On Cereal Boxes Prove Easy Pickings For Thieves</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Toy California raisins attached to boxes of Post
Raisin Bran have proved to be easy pickings for light-fingered
supermarket patrons.
   Of 36 cereal boxes recently put on the shelves of one grocery
store, 30 were relieved of their raisin figures. The figures are
based on the raisins seen dancing to ``Heard It Through the
Grapevine'' in TV commercials.
   The raisin figures were put in separate containers glued to the
tops of the cereal boxes. General Foods Corp. launched the
promotion two weeks ago.
   ``Maybe one or two people actually bothered to buy the cereal to
get the toy,'' said Gary Ringer, night manager of a supermarket.
``The rest we just packed up and shipped back to the warehouse and
said, `Thanks, but we'd rather just have our money back.'
   ``No one's going to buy a mangled box.''
</TEXT>
