<1ST_LINE>r p PM-BRF--RichardsSpeech     07-14 0122</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Richards Speech,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Democratic Keynote Address Lost in Computer Glitch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A draft version of Ann Richards' keynote
speech to the Democratic National Convention was lost in a computer
glitch, but a speech writer helping the Texas state treasurer was
able to reconstruct the address.
   The computer took the speech, which was about 95 percent
complete, on Tuesday while John Sherman, a speech writer for the
Democratic National Committee, was revising the address.
   Sherman, working from earlier drafts and Ms. Richards' notes,
was able to reconstruct the half-hour address on Wednesday.
   ``I don't trust machines and never have,'' said Ms. Richards,
who finally was able to begin practicing her delivery in
preparation for the Monday night address.
