<1ST_LINE>r i PM-India-CopterCrash     07-14 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-India-Copter Crash,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Helicopter Crash Kills Seven Pilgrims</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A helicopter ferrying Hindu pilgrims to
a cave temple in northern Kashmir state crashed today, and all
seven people on board were killed, Indian news agencies reported.
   Among the victims were the two crew members of the
state-operated helicopter service, the United News of India and
Press Trust of India reported.
   The pilgrims were on their way to Vaishno Devi, a temple in the
Himalayas dedicated to three mother Goddesses of Hinduism, the
reports said. Tens of thousands of pilgrims annually visit the
shrine, which is 280 miles north of New Delhi.
   The cause of the crash was not immediately known.
</TEXT>
