<2ND_LINE>PM-Water Toy Recall,170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Water, Snake Toys Recalled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Water toys and a squeaking toy snake are being
recalled because of potential choking and lead hazards, the
Consumer Product Safety Commission said today.
   Beachcombers International of Fort Myers, Fla. said consumers
should remove the toys from children and return them to the
retailer for a refund. Toys involved are:
   _Big Mouth Fish, Hippo and Frog, plastic wind-up water toys
labeled ``Masudaya 1976 Made in Hong Kong.'' About 8,000 have been
sold nationally for about $2 each.
   _Devil Fish, a wind-up toy in the shape of a fish. Imported from
Hong Kong and sold for $2 in New Jersey and Virginia.
   _Lively Squeaking Snake, a plastic cobra snake 21 inches long
from China, sold nationally for $1.
   The toy snake contains an excessive amount of lead in the
surface coating, and the other toys have small parts which could
pose a choking hazard, the Safety Commission reports.
   People needing more information can call Beachcombers
International at 1-813-731-2111 or the Safety Commission at
1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
