   The last Volkswagen made in America
rolls off the assembly line today when the West German automaker
closes its only U.S. assembly plant in an area already hit hard by
declining manufacturing.
   The company cited slumping sales and increased competition for
the closure, although many workers blame trade policies.
   The Volkswagen still will be sold in the United States. Jetta
models will be imported from West Germany and Golf models from
Mexico, the company said.
