<1ST_LINE>r f AM-AutoProdn     07-14 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Prodn,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
135,948 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
124,029, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 158,532 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 96,463 cars this week,
compared with 84,104 a week ago and 91,804 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 39,485,
compared with last week's 39,925 and last year's 66,728.
   Canadian automakers were to build 8,495 cars this week, down
from 12,343 a week ago and up from last year's 4,601.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 7,373, compared
with 15,690 a week ago and 9,846 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
